Hi all, well, what a win. You could feel the energy from the crowd behind her supporting her. When she missed the first dart for victory, you could hear the gasps of the crowd.

Then, just as she was throwing the winning dart, there was an absolute silence for a second, then the eruption of joy.

A true history making moment that will be never forgotten, as it proves that woman & men are EQUALLY just as good at all different types of sports.

As aside from football, snooker is another where woman are making serious in roads in recent years, and their very good, particularly in Asia.

snippet.textDisplay:
So.....the girl beat the man.
I thought it was supposed to be a Darts tournament ?
Darts, along with many other sports, is where men and women are on a level playing field.
The Girl won fair and square, she was congratulated by her opponent. She was cheered by the crowd, which appeared to be predominantly men, and presumably out of respect for her skills as a Dart player, NOT as a woman.
She did very well and good luck to her, why turn it into a Politically correct, feminist empowerment trip ?
How patronising for the Girl who won the Darts Championship.
What's wrong with people ?
